<br>
I don't mind working with bards or shamans or anyone for that matter.<br>
Yes, I find it irritating when a bard overrides my mez, but I can live with it. I'm just irritated about wasting mana, that's about all. If the bard felt he needed to mez the mob, then the bard didn't feel safe.<br>
That to me means I was either not fast enough or I need to talk with the bard to see why he doesn't feel safe with my mezzes.<br>
Either way - it's not hitting anyone = good.<br>
As for the cases you state above - all of those are valid emergencies and any enchanter who gets mad at you for saving their butt (or the clerics) is an idiot. You may save my butt any time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
If you jump in and mez a mob that was beating on someone, then that mob is now crowd controlled and can be killed.<br>
He's not beating on anyone and this is a GOOD thing. <br>
