<br>
1) Enchanters are VERY territorial when it comes to mezzing, because its one of 4 things we have that people want in thier groups. Mezzing, Clarity, Speed, Slow.<br>
<br>
  a) Mezing can also be done by Necros, and Bards, and can be not even needed in AE or Off-Tank Groups.<br>
<br>
  b) Clarity we are the only class who can do this BUT: Wizards gain self clarity from manaskin, familurs.. Druids gain self clarity from thier top wolf forms and potc/g.... Shamen gain self clarity with Bear Form and Canabillize(sp?).. Necros gain self clarity with thier lich line, and can donate mana.. Mages can donate mod rods which are large Canabilize Spell Items...Beastlords if i remember correctly get a group breeze type spell.. So With the exception of Rangers, Shadoknights, and Clerics we really aren't NEEDED for this, just a nice bonus.<br>
<br>
  c) Speed well we are the kings of speed, but Shamen can speed almost as well, and Bards can speed a little slower than Shamen.<br>
<br>
  d) Slow... Shamen are the kings of this, we can't even compare to them the way they can compare to us with speed.<br>
<br>
  e) So basically we get really upset when our MAIN function gets taken over (and nullified by ie. Your spell does not take hold) by someone else in the group.<br>
<br>
2) Enchanters can and do have REALLY bad days, I think my personal best was 16 deaths in 20 mins... and when a group dies because of adds, the Enchanter is blamed either by the group or by themselves or both.. this makes for a really ticked off enchanter.<br>
<br>
3) Communication is the key... if someone ignores what your saying /tell them to make sure they got the message.. Not saying that you didn't make enough effort, just saying this as a suggestion.<br>
<br>
I do agree with your 4 emergencies, especially the cleric... usually when something is beating on me I will stun it... if im in trouble I won't bitch about you mezzing it... but i might bitch about my mez going off right after yours and getting the won't take hold message... (GOD I HATE THAT) our mezzes last longer they should overwrite Bard Mezes... but oh well...<br>
<br>
